---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Stack from '../../components/Stack.astro';

const usageSnippet = `---
import { Stack } from 'comet-astro';
---

<Stack 
  direction="vertical" 
  gap="md" 
  align="stretch"
  justify="start"
>
  <div>Item 1</div>
  <div>Item 2</div>
  <div>Item 3</div>
</Stack>`;
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Stack"
  description="WCAG AAA compliant flexbox layout component with responsive spacing and semantic HTML support."
>
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-base text-slate-100">
      Stack provides accessible flexbox layouts for arranging content vertically
      or horizontally with consistent spacing. It supports semantic HTML
      elements, ARIA labeling, and responsive design patterns.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      The component automatically handles focus management for interactive
      content, provides visual debugging tools for development, and ensures
      proper contrast ratios and borders in all themes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Props</h2>
    <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          direction?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Layout direction. Choose <code>"vertical"</code> or <code
            >"horizontal"</code
          >. Defaults to <code>"vertical"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          gap?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Spacing between items. Choose <code>"none"</code>, <code>"xs"</code>, <code
            >"sm"</code
          >,
          <code>"md"</code>, <code>"lg"</code>, <code>"xl"</code>, <code
            >"2xl"</code
          >,
          <code>"3xl"</code>, or <code>"4xl"</code>. Defaults to <code
            >"md"</code
          >.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          align?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Cross-axis alignment. Choose <code>"start"</code>, <code
            >"center"</code
          >,
          <code>"end"</code>, <code>"stretch"</code>, or <code>"baseline"</code
          >. Defaults to <code>"stretch"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          justify?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Main-axis alignment. Choose <code>"start"</code>, <code>"center"</code
          >,
          <code>"end"</code>, <code>"between"</code>, <code>"around"</code>, or
          <code>"evenly"</code>. Defaults to <code>"start"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          wrap?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Allow flex wrapping. Defaults to <code>false</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          responsive?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Responsive gap variations. Object with <code>sm</code>, <code>md</code
          >,
          <code>lg</code>, <code>xl</code> breakpoint keys.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          as?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Semantic HTML element. Choose <code>"div"</code>, <code
            >"section"</code
          >,
          <code>"article"</code>, <code>"nav"</code>, <code>"ul"</code>, <code
            >"ol"</code
          >, etc. Defaults to <code>"div"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          role?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          ARIA role for accessibility context.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          ariaLabel?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Accessible label for screen readers.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          debug?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Show visual debugging information. Defaults to <code>false</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Usage</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Import the component and wrap your content. Stack automatically applies
      flexbox layout with the specified direction, spacing, and alignment. Use
      semantic HTML elements for better accessibility.
    </p>
    <pre
      class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-slate-700/70 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-sm text-slate-50 shadow-inner">
      <code class="language-astro">{usageSnippet}</code>
    </pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Direction Examples</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <!-- Vertical Stack -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Vertical Stack</h3>
        <div
          class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-6 shadow-sm"
        >
          <Stack direction="vertical" gap="md">
            <div
              class="bg-blue-500/20 p-4 rounded text-center text-sm text-slate-200"
            >
              Item 1
            </div>
            <div
              class="bg-blue-500/20 p-4 rounded text-center text-sm text-slate-200"
            >
              Item 2
            </div>
            <div
              class="bg-blue-500/20 p-4 rounded text-center text-sm text-slate-200"
            >
              Item 3
            </div>
          </Stack>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Horizontal Stack -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Horizontal Stack</h3>
        <div
          class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-6 shadow-sm"
        >
          <Stack direction="horizontal" gap="md">
            <div
              class="bg-green-500/20 p-4 rounded text-center text-sm text-slate-200"
            >
              Item 1
            </div>
            <div
              class="bg-green-500/20 p-4 rounded text-center text-sm text-slate-200"
            >
              Item 2
            </div>
            <div
              class="bg-green-500/20 p-4 rounded text-center text-sm text-slate-200"
            >
              Item 3
            </div>
          </Stack>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Gap Sizes</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Gap Size Demonstrations -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Gap Size Comparison</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
          {
            ['none', 'xs', 'sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl', '2xl', '3xl'].map(
              (gapSize) => (
                <div key={gapSize} class="space-y-2">
                  <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-200 capitalize">
                    {gapSize}{' '}
                    {gapSize === 'none'
                      ? '(0px)'
                      : gapSize === 'xs'
                        ? '(4px)'
                        : gapSize === 'sm'
                          ? '(8px)'
                          : gapSize === 'md'
                            ? '(16px)'
                            : gapSize === 'lg'
                              ? '(24px)'
                              : gapSize === 'xl'
                                ? '(32px)'
                                : gapSize === '2xl'
                                  ? '(48px)'
                                  : '(64px)'}
                  </h4>
                  <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm">
                    <Stack direction="vertical" gap={gapSize}>
                      <div class="bg-purple-500/20 p-2 rounded text-center text-xs text-slate-200">
                        Item
                      </div>
                      <div class="bg-purple-500/20 p-2 rounded text-center text-xs text-slate-200">
                        Item
                      </div>
                      <div class="bg-purple-500/20 p-2 rounded text-center text-xs text-slate-200">
                        Item
                      </div>
                    </Stack>
                  </div>
                </div>
              )
            )
          }
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Alignment Examples</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <!-- Align Examples -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Cross-Axis Alignment</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {
            ['start', 'center', 'end', 'stretch'].map((alignValue) => (
              <div key={alignValue} class="space-y-2">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-200 capitalize">
                  {alignValue}
                </h4>
                <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm">
                  <Stack
                    direction="horizontal"
                    gap="sm"
                    align={alignValue}
                    class="h-24"
                  >
                    <div class="bg-amber-500/20 p-2 rounded text-center text-xs text-slate-200 flex-shrink-0">
                      Small
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-amber-500/20 p-4 rounded text-center text-xs text-slate-200 flex-shrink-0">
                      Medium
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-amber-500/20 p-6 rounded text-center text-xs text-slate-200 flex-shrink-0">
                      Large
                    </div>
                  </Stack>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Justify Examples -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Main-Axis Alignment</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {
            ['start', 'center', 'end', 'between', 'around', 'evenly'].map(
              (justifyValue) => (
                <div key={justifyValue} class="space-y-2">
                  <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-200 capitalize">
                    {justifyValue}
                  </h4>
                  <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm">
                    <Stack
                      direction="horizontal"
                      gap="none"
                      justify={justifyValue}
                    >
                      <div class="bg-cyan-500/20 p-3 rounded text-center text-xs text-slate-200">
                        A
                      </div>
                      <div class="bg-cyan-500/20 p-3 rounded text-center text-xs text-slate-200">
                        B
                      </div>
                      <div class="bg-cyan-500/20 p-3 rounded text-center text-xs text-slate-200">
                        C
                      </div>
                    </Stack>
                  </div>
                </div>
              )
            )
          }
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Advanced Features</h2>

    <!-- Responsive Gaps -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Responsive Gaps</h3>
      <div
        class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-6 shadow-sm"
      >
        <Stack
          direction="vertical"
          gap="xs"
          responsive={{ sm: 'sm', md: 'md', lg: 'lg', xl: 'xl' }}
        >
          <div
            class="bg-indigo-500/20 p-4 rounded text-center text-sm text-slate-200"
          >
            Responsive Gap: xs → sm → md → lg → xl
          </div>
          <div
            class="bg-indigo-500/20 p-4 rounded text-center text-sm text-slate-200"
          >
            Resize browser to see gap changes
          </div>
          <div
            class="bg-indigo-500/20 p-4 rounded text-center text-sm text-slate-200"
          >
            Mobile-first responsive design
          </div>
        </Stack>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Semantic HTML -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Semantic HTML</h3>
      <div
        class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-6 shadow-sm"
      >
        <Stack
          as="nav"
          direction="horizontal"
          gap="lg"
          justify="between"
          align="center"
          ariaLabel="Main navigation"
        >
          <div class="font-semibold text-slate-100">Logo</div>
          <Stack as="ul" direction="horizontal" gap="md" role="menubar">
            <li>
              <a href="#" class="text-slate-300 hover:text-slate-100 text-sm"
                >Home</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="#" class="text-slate-300 hover:text-slate-100 text-sm"
                >About</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="#" class="text-slate-300 hover:text-slate-100 text-sm"
                >Contact</a
              >
            </li>
          </Stack>
        </Stack>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Common Patterns</h2>

    <!-- Card Layout -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Card Layout</h3>
      <div
        class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-6 shadow-sm"
      >
        <Stack as="article" direction="vertical" gap="lg" class="max-w-md">
          <div class="bg-slate-800/60 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <Stack direction="vertical" gap="md">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">Card Title</h4>
              <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">
                Card description with proper spacing and hierarchy.
              </p>
              <Stack direction="horizontal" gap="sm" justify="end">
                <button
                  class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-600 text-white text-xs rounded"
                  >Cancel</button
                >
                <button class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-600 text-white text-xs rounded"
                  >Confirm</button
                >
              </Stack>
            </Stack>
          </div>
        </Stack>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Dashboard Layout -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Dashboard Layout</h3>
      <div
        class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-6 shadow-sm"
      >
        <Stack as="main" direction="vertical" gap="xl">
          <Stack
            as="header"
            direction="horizontal"
            gap="md"
            justify="between"
            align="center"
          >
            <h1 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-100">Dashboard</h1>
            <button class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white text-sm rounded"
              >New Item</button
            >
          </Stack>

          <Stack direction="horizontal" gap="lg" wrap={true}>
            {
              Array.from({ length: 3 }, (_, index) => (
                <div key={index} class="flex-1 min-w-48">
                  <Stack
                    direction="vertical"
                    gap="sm"
                    class="bg-slate-800/60 p-4 rounded-lg"
                  >
                    <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-100">
                      Widget {index + 1}
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">
                      Widget content with consistent spacing.
                    </p>
                    <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-400">
                      {(index + 1) * 24}
                    </div>
                  </Stack>
                </div>
              ))
            }
          </Stack>
        </Stack>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Form Layout -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Form Layout</h3>
      <div
        class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-6 shadow-sm"
      >
        <Stack as="form" direction="vertical" gap="lg" class="max-w-md">
          <Stack direction="vertical" gap="sm">
            <label class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-200">Email</label>
            <input
              type="email"
              class="px-3 py-2 bg-slate-800 border border-slate-600 rounded text-slate-100 text-sm"
            />
          </Stack>

          <Stack direction="vertical" gap="sm">
            <label class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-200">Message</label>
            <textarea
              rows="4"
              class="px-3 py-2 bg-slate-800 border border-slate-600 rounded text-slate-100 text-sm"
            ></textarea>
          </Stack>

          <Stack direction="horizontal" gap="md" justify="end">
            <button
              type="button"
              class="px-4 py-2 bg-slate-600 text-white text-sm rounded"
              >Cancel</button
            >
            <button
              type="submit"
              class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white text-sm rounded"
              >Submit</button
            >
          </Stack>
        </Stack>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Accessibility</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Stack components support semantic HTML elements and ARIA labeling for
      proper accessibility, with appropriate contrast ratios that exceed WCAG
      AAA requirements and adjust automatically for high contrast mode.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Focus management is handled automatically for interactive content, and
      debug mode provides visual feedback during development without affecting
      production accessibility. All spacing follows consistent design tokens.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      The component respects user preferences for reduced motion and provides
      semantic structure through proper HTML elements and ARIA roles. Responsive
      gaps ensure proper spacing across all device sizes.
    </p>

    <div
      class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
    >
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-3">
        Gap Size Reference
      </h3>
      <div class="grid gap-2 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs">
          <span class="text-slate-300">none</span>
          <span class="text-slate-400">0px</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs">
          <span class="text-slate-300">xs</span>
          <span class="text-slate-400">4px</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs">
          <span class="text-slate-300">sm</span>
          <span class="text-slate-400">8px</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs">
          <span class="text-slate-300">md</span>
          <span class="text-slate-400">16px</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs">
          <span class="text-slate-300">lg</span>
          <span class="text-slate-400">24px</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs">
          <span class="text-slate-300">xl</span>
          <span class="text-slate-400">32px</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs">
          <span class="text-slate-300">2xl</span>
          <span class="text-slate-400">48px</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs">
          <span class="text-slate-300">3xl</span>
          <span class="text-slate-400">64px</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
